 <datafield tag="245" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
  <subfield code="a">Unified cluster-based description of valence bands in AlIr, RuAl(2), RuGa(3) and Al–TM quasicrystalline approximants</subfield>
  <subfield code="9">IOP</subfield>
 </datafield>
 <datafield tag="520" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
  <subfield code="a">Formation of the valence bands in AlIr, RuAl(2) and RuGa(3) was analysed on the basis of Wannier functions. It was sufficient to consider nine (s-, p- and d-like) Wannier functions per cluster centred on each transition metal for describing the valence bands. As in the case of Al-Cu-Ir quasicrystalline approximant, which we reported previously [Kitahara K, Takagiwa Y and Kimura K 2015 J. Phys. Soc. Jpn. 84 014703-1-8], covalent bonds between clusters form where the distance between neighbouring clusters is about 0.3 nm, making conduction states as antibonding functions. sp (3) d (2)-, sp (3)- and p(y) -like Wannier functions are used for the covalent bonds in AlIr, RuAl(2) and RuGa(3), respectively.</subfield>
  <subfield code="9">IOP</subfield>
 </datafield>
